{{update|inaccurate=yes|date=February 2018}}
This is a list of Mexican states by their respective homicide data.
== Methodology ==
The [[Instituto Nacional de Estadística y Geografía|National Institute of Statistic and Geography]] released information of homicides for the [[States of Mexico|31 federal states]] and the [[Mexican Federal District|Federal District]] of [[Mexico]]. In the year 2011 there were 27,199 homicides in [[Mexico]]. The state of [[Chihuahua (state)|Chihuahua]] ranked number one with the most homicides in the country, the least was [[Baja California Sur]]. For Mexico there were 24 homicides for every 100,000 inhabitants.
