{{Infobox Government agency |agency_name = National Population and Family Planning Commission |nativename = |nativename_a = {{nobold|{{lang|zh-hans|国家人口和计划生育委员会}}}} |nativename_r = {{small|Guójiā Rénkǒu Hé Jìhuà Shēngyù Wěiyuánhuì}} |logo = |logo_width = |logo_caption = |seal = |seal_width = |seal_caption = |formed = 1981 |preceding1 = |preceding2 = |dissolved = March 2013 |superseding = [[National Health and Family Planning Commission]] |jurisdiction = {{PRC}} |headquarters = [[Beijing]] |employees = |budget = |minister1_name = |minister1_pfo = |chief1_name = |chief1_position = |chief2_name = |chief2_position = |parent_agency = [[State Council of the People's Republic of China|State Council]] |child1_agency = |child2_agency = |website = [http://www.chinapop.gov.cn www.chinapop.gov.cn] |footnotes = }} '''National Population and Family Planning Commission''' ('''NPFPC''', 2003-2013), formerly '''National Family Planning Commission''' (1981-2003), of the [[Government of the People's Republic of China]] was the state agency responsible for [[population]] and [[family planning]] in the [[People's Republic of China]]. The Commission was dissolved and superseded by the [[National Health and Family Planning Commission]] in March 2013, during the first session of the 12th National People's Congress.
The agency was managed by a minister and four vice ministers.<ref>[http://www.npfpc.gov.cn/en National Population and Family Planning Commission of China] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20061201170356/http://www.npfpc.gov.cn/en/ |date=2006-12-01 }}</ref>
